https://cloudgateuniverse.com/docs/customize-ui-plugin-tabHow to customize the UI 'Plugin' tab
This page describes how to customize the 'Plugin' tab on the UI.

 

The 'Plugin' tab can be customized in the following way:

A developer can change the text of the 'Plugin' tab.
A developer can set the position of the 'Plugin' tab to the most left position of the navigation bar.
A developer can, in extend to the previous point, change the home page to one of his 'Plugin' pages.
 

Let's give an example on how to do this.

 

1. The 'Plugin' tab
The 'Plugin' tab is the tab on the UI shown in the next image.



 

2. UCI configuration
A new UI section with the name 'plugin_ui' must be created.

 

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name 'New name of the plugin tab'

option home '1'

option home_page_name 'Name of your application page'

 

name: name of the 'Plugin' tab. HTML tags are supported. 
home 1 or 0. If set to 1, the 'Plugin' tab becomes the new home page. The tab will be located on the most left side of the navigation bar. 
home_page_name: if set, the home page will be the page you registered via the cg_ui_register_page SDK call. If not set, the first available page becomes the home page.

 

In case you want to do this via command line:

 

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui=ui

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.name='New name of the plugin tab'

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.home='1'

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.home_page_name='Name of your application page'

uci commit m2mweb

 

The next subsections will show you the different options.

 

2.1 Change the 'Plugin' text
Let's change the 'Plugin' text to 'Energy meters'. We also want it in red, bold and underlined.

 

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui=ui

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.name='<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

uci commit m2mweb

 

The configuration looks like ...

 

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name '<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

 

... and the UI looks like: 



 

2.2 Setting the 'Plugin' tab as a home page
To set the first available page as a home page, do:

 

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui=ui

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.name='<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.home=1

uci commit m2mweb

 

The configuration looks like ...

 

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name '<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

option home '1'

 

.. and the UI looks like:



 

Notice the 'Plugin' tab is moved to the most left position. 

When setting the 'Plugin' tab as homepage, the 'Home' tab will be renamed to 'Summary'. (Not shown in the picture above.)

 

2.3 Setting the 'Plugin' tab as a home page with a specific application page
To set a specific application page as home page, just add the home_page_name option. The name is the one you registered via the cg_ui_register_page SDK call.

 

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui=ui

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.name='<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.home=1

uci set m2mweb.plugin_ui.home_page_name='ui_simple example page'

uci commit m2mweb

 

The configuration looks like ...

 

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name '<font color="red"><strong><u>Energy meters</u></strong></font>'

option home '1'

option home_page_name 'ui_simple example page'

 

