3 SDK example
In this example, we create an application which registers three plugin pages. One of the pages will be set as our new home page.

3.1 package
Starting from the top-level directory of the SDK, create a new directory 'my_app' in the package directory.

 

mkdir package/my_app

mkdir package/my_app/src (source code of our application)

mkdir -p package/my_app/files/www (Web page of our application)

 

3.1.1 Makefile
In the new directory, create a Makefile with the next content:

 

include $(TOPDIR)/rules.mk

 

PKG_NAME:=my_app

PKG_VERSION:=1.0

 

include $(INCLUDE_DIR)/package.mk

include $(INCLUDE_DIR)/nls.mk

 

define Package/my_app

SECTION:=base

CATEGORY:=Base system

TITLE:=My Application

DEPENDS:=+libcg

endef

 

define Build/Prepare

$(call Build/Prepare/Default)

$(CP) -l src/* $(PKG_BUILD_DIR)/

$(CP) -r files/* $(PKG_BUILD_DIR)

endef

 

define Build/Compile

$(MAKE) -C $(PKG_BUILD_DIR) CC="$(TARGET_CC)" LD="$(TARGET_LD)" CFLAGS="$(TARGET_CFLAGS) $(TARGET_CPPFLAGS) $(FPIC)" LDFLAGS="$(TARGET_LDFLAGS)"

endef

 

define Package/my_app/install

$(INSTALL_DIR) $(1)/my_app/www

$(CP) $(PKG_BUILD_DIR)/my_app $(1)/isv

$(CP) -r $(PKG_BUILD_DIR)/www/* $(1)/my_app/www

endef

 

$(eval $(call BuildPackage,my_app))

 

3.1.2 Web pages
Create three extra HTML files in the package/my_app/files/www directory.

 

echo "Welcome to page 1." > package/my_app/files/www/page1.html

echo "Welcome to page 2." > package/my_app/files/www/page2.html

echo "Welcome to page 3." > package/my_app/files/www/page3.html

 

3.1.3 Application
Create a main.c file in package/my_app/src and add the next content:

 

#include <stdio.h>

#include <unistd.h>

 

#include <libcg/cg_general.h>

#include <libcg/cg_ui.h>

 

#define CONFIG_SYMLINK "www_my_app/"

 

#define HTML_PAGE_1 "page1.html"

#define HTML_PAGE_2 "page2.html"

#define HTML_PAGE_3 "page3.html"

 

#define NAME_PAGE_1 "First page"

#define NAME_PAGE_2 "Second page"

#define NAME_PAGE_3 "Third page"

 

int main (void)

{

cg_status_t cg_status;

 

cg_status = cg_init("my_app");

 

if (cg_status != CG_STATUS_OK) {

fprintf(stderr, "Error initializing my_app SDK\n");

return 1;

}

/**

* In the m2mweb configuration file, we specified a symlink www_my_app where our HTML

* files are located. We use this symlink to register our pages.

*/

 

cg_status |= cg_ui_register_page(NAME_PAGE_1, CONFIG_SYMLINK HTML_PAGE_1);

cg_status |= cg_ui_register_page(NAME_PAGE_2, CONFIG_SYMLINK HTML_PAGE_2);

cg_status |= cg_ui_register_page(NAME_PAGE_3, CONFIG_SYMLINK HTML_PAGE_3);

if(cg_status != CG_STATUS_OK){

cg_system_log(CG_LOG_ERR, "Error registering pages\n");

goto faulty;

}

 

while (1) {

sleep(1);

}

//Never gets here.

 

faulty:

cg_ui_deregister_page(NAME_PAGE_1);

cg_ui_deregister_page(NAME_PAGE_2);

cg_ui_deregister_page(NAME_PAGE_3);

cg_deinit();

 

return 0;

}

 

In this example, we create three pages via the SDK call cg_ui_register_page. The page names are 'First page', 'Second page' and 'Third page'. We need these names later. Every page name is linked to one HTML page.

 

3.1.4 Application Makefile
Create a Makefile in package/my_app/src with the next content:

 

all: my_app

 

OBJS = $(patsubst %.c,%.o,$(wildcard *.c))

 

DEBUG = -ggdb #-O0

override LDFLAGS += -lsms -lcg -lpthread -ljson-c

 

%.o: %.c

$(CC) $(CFLAGS) $(DEBUG) -fPIC -Wall -Werror -I. -std=gnu99 -c $(<) -o $(@)

 

my_app: $(OBJS)

$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -o $(@) $(^) $(LDFLAGS)

 

clean:

rm -f $(OBJS) $(BINS) 

 

.PHONY: all clean my_app

 

The my_app directory now looks like:

 

package/my_app/

├── files

│   └── www

│         ├── page1.html

│         ├── page2.html

│         └── page3.html

├── Makefile

└── src

 ├── main.c

 └── Makefile

 

3 directories, 6 files

 

3.2 Configuration
From the SDK root, create a file m2mweb in config/config

For now, add the next line:

 

package m2mweb

 

3.2.1 Symlinks
We need to tell the GUI that our HTML pages are located in a different path. This can be done by adding a symlink. To the config/config/m2mweb configuration, add the following:

 

config default 'www_my_app'

option path '/rom/mnt/cust/my_app/www/'

 

Note that this path is specified in the Makefile.

 

3.2.2 Plugin configuration
Now, we can configure the custom plugin. We want the 'Plugin' tab to be renamed to 'My App' and show it in bold. It must be set as the new home page and the home page must be 'First page'. That is the page we registered in the cg_ui_register_page SDK call.

 

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name '<strong>My App</strong>'

option home '1'

option home_page_name 'First page'

 

The complete configuration file looks like:

 

package m2mweb

config default 'www_my_app'

option path '/rom/mnt/cust/my_app/www/'

config ui 'plugin_ui'

option name '<strong>My App</strong>'

option home '1'

option home_page_name 'First page'

 

3.3 Compile
Enable the my_app application first.

 

make menuconfig -> Base system -> my_app

Keep pressing the space bar until you see a *

Exit and save the changes.

make V=99

 

Now upload your application to the CloudGate.

 

3.4 UI
After rebooting, log in again in the UI. 



Notice that the home page is set the Page 1.

 

